==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Ambiguity
<hw>Am`bi*gu"i*ty</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>; <plu><it>pl.</it>
<plw>Ambiguities</plw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>.</plu> <ety>[L.
<ets>ambiguitas</ets>, fr. <ets>ambiguus</ets>: cf. F.
<ets>ambiguit⟦eacute⟧</ets>.]</ety> <def>The quality or state of being
ambiguous; doubtfulness or uncertainty, particularly as to the
signification of language, arising from its admitting of more than one
meaning; an equivocal word or expression.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>No shadow of <qex>ambiguity</qex> can rest upon the course to be
pursued.</q> <rj><qau>I. Taylor.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The words are of single signification, without any
<qex>ambiguity</qex>.</q> <rj><qau>South.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Ambiguous</ent>⟦br⟧
